parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel valve diaphragm can cause gasoline to leak onto the engine, posing a significant risk of fire and potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Gasoline dripping from the fuel valve
fuel leaking onto the engine block
fuel puddles forming under the motorcycle
fuel valve diaphragm failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the petcock valve can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to engine stalling, fires, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the rider's safety.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel control valve
fuel leaks from the on and reserve selection
engine stalling
sputtering
chrome clutch cover peeling up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unstable ride and clutch issues can cause the motorcycle to behave erratically, making it difficult to control and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The motorcycle has a rough ride
the tires "skip/hop" or vibrate while driving at 25 mph and above
the clutch has play or feels loose
the motorcycle feels unstable or unpredictable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tire vibration and wobbling can cause the motorcycle to lose traction, making it difficult to control and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The tires vibrate or wobble while driving
the motorcycle feels unstable or unpredictable
the tires "skip/hop" or jump while driving at 25 mph and above.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch failure can cause the motorcycle to lose power or stall, making it difficult to control and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The clutch feels soft or spongy
the clutch has play or feels loose
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the motorcycle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage gears can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when rear-ended by another vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into first gear or any other gear
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The knocking noise in the V-twin engine can be a sign of premature wear on engine components, potentially leading to engine failure, decreased performance, and reduced fuel efficiency.
symptoms: Knocking or tapping noise from the engine
noise disappears when the clutch is partially engaged
noise is more pronounced when the engine is under load.
